{
  "stem": "24397.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And suddenly, they're-- say, they gave them a choice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You can either get a couple of evacuees or a family from London that's being evacuated or a couple of soldiers billeted because there was some station near there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was according to how many rooms you had in the house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they, they had to go for one of those.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they chose the lesser of these three evils, which they thought they'll get a couple of kids.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Well, when they saw who they got, they-- they didn't like Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The woman told me many times that she thought the best thing that ever happened was what Hitler was doing to the Jews, although at that time I don't think she really knew what was happening to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But she just knew what bad things are happening.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I had strict rules that I was only allowed inside the house for meals and to sleep.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I had to take the dog for a walk before going to school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So most of the time, I-- because English weather can be pretty miserable-- I used to hang around the doorways of shops, asking people the time, so I knew when I could, could go back into the house.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And didn't have a proper bed to sleep in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I had just one of those army cots with just a sheet on it, nothing underneath it, and a blanket over the top of me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But the strange thing about it is there were so many nice people there who would have offered me a home and wanted me to stay there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "What I didn't realize is that I had the power within me to complain about it.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
